{
  "text": "For in vivo studies, Rac1 inhibitor, NSC23766 (NSC), was administrated daily from days 7 to 13 after stroke (7 days, 4.0 mg/kg, i.p.). Control mice received the equal amount of vehicle. While most of the published work used 2.5 mg/kg/ day in mice [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , we chose 4.0 mg/kg/day to ensure an effective inhibition and found no evidence for toxicity at this dose. For in vitro experiments, the concentration of 30 \u03bcM NSC was used [CITATION_3] . BrdU (bromodeoxyuridine) was injected 7 days after stroke (dose, 50 mg/kg, i.p./8 h for 24 h) [CITATION_4] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "46248311",
